The KDF recruiting team on Monday locked out hundreds of youths in Malindi for arriving late and for body ailments.Others who were locked out had skin diseases, while some had not met the minimum academic qualifications of D+ required.The drive, which attracted more than 700 youths, also saw many being locked out because they did not meet the age and height requirements. The cut-off age is 25 years.Some youths gave up after they found the exercise too tough.Recruiting team leader Colonel Oloo said the drive was transparent and all those locked out went home satisfied.During the recruitment, Oloo talked to residents and urged them to ask questions about the exercise. The majority of them said they were satisfied with his responses.